  </section>

  <!-- ========== SECTION 6 — SG GEO BENCHMARKS ========== -->
  <section class="section" id="sg-geo-benchmarks" aria-label="Singapore GEO market benchmarks">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">SG Benchmarks</p>
        <h2>What GEO actually looks like in the Singapore market right now</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar-prose reveal">
        <p>The numbers being thrown around in most AI-search pitches are mostly global. Singapore is its own AI search market with its own dynamics. Here is what we observe across the audits and accounts Jraft runs.</p>

        <p><strong>AI search adoption in SG.</strong> 60.9% of Singapore consumers use generative AI for research at least monthly (NUS / Microsoft Asia 2025 disclosure). ChatGPT crossed one million weekly active users in Singapore in late 2025. The SG ChatGPT user base is older and more commercial in intent than the global average — heavy use by procurement managers, parents researching education, and patients researching healthcare.</p>

        <p><strong>AI citation overlap with Google.</strong> Below 20%. The brands AI cites for commercial queries in SG are not the brands ranking page one on Google for the same queries. The two surfaces use different signals and reward different content.</p>

        <p><strong>SG-specific citation sources LLMs trust.</strong> Wikipedia (English and Mandarin), <code>.gov.sg</code> domains, established SG business media (Business Times, CNA, The Edge Singapore, SBR), Tripadvisor for hospitality, Google reviews above 4.5 stars with detailed text, and category-specific directories (SMA for clinics, MOE-listed centres for education). The trust hierarchy is similar to Google&rsquo;s but the weights differ — LLMs weight Wikipedia and third-party media higher than Google does.</p>

        <p><strong>Schema implementation in SG SME.</strong> From the audits we run, fewer than 30% of SG SME sites have FAQPage, Organization, or Service schema correctly implemented. Of those who do, fewer than half have <code>llms.txt</code> deployed. The technical bar to outrank competitors in AI answers is currently lower than it will ever be again.</p>
      </div>

